Welcome to Relay Node - your gateway to the distributed ASCII cinema network.
Mission Brief
This network serves as a hub for ASCII art streaming, telnet cinema, and text-based entertainment distribution. Connect to our nodes via SSH or Telnet to experience classic films, animations, and live art performances rendered in pure text.
Quick Connect

Browse our transmission archive or check the current streaming schedule.

https://example.com/about/.body:
About Relay Node
Relay Node is a distributed network for ASCII cinema streaming. Our mission is to preserve and share the art of text-based entertainment across the global network.
The Network
Our infrastructure spans multiple continents, with relay nodes positioned strategically to minimize latency and maximize uptime. Each node operates independently while maintaining synchronization with the central archive.
Technology Stack

Streaming Protocol: Custom optimized for low-bandwidth ASCII transmission
Encoding: UTF-8 with ANSI color support
Clients: Standard SSH/Telnet compatible

History
The Relay Node network was established to bring classic ASCII cinema to a new generation of viewers. What started as a single server has grown into a global mesh of interconnected nodes.
Contact
For node operators and contributors, reach out via the standard encrypted channels.

https://example.com/blog/ascii-art-showc.body:
This month we highlight exceptional ASCII artists contributing to the network archive.
Featured Works
"Digital Sunset" by NodeRunner
A stunning landscape piece using advanced ANSI coloring techniques. The gradient work demonstrates mastery of the 256-color palette.
"Binary Dreams" by CipherArt
An abstract exploration of data visualization rendered in pure monochrome. Each character carefully chosen to create depth and movement.
Submit Your Work
Artists interested in contributing to the network archive should prepare their pieces in the following formats:

Maximum dimensions: 80x24 characters
Encoding: UTF-8
Color: ANSI 256 or 16-color compatible

Contact the archive maintainers via encrypted channel for submission guidelines.
